article.description: — Moses Wood and Chris Austin scored 18 points apiece to help Portland get past Pacific 75-69 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Wood, Austin lead Portland over Pacific 75-69
article.linkText: Wood, Austin lead Portland over Pacific 75-69
article.story: STOCKTON, Calif. -- — Moses Wood and Chris Austin scored 18 points apiece to help Portland get past Pacific 75-69 on Thursday night. Tyler Robertson added 15 points and eight rebounds for the Pilots (17-12, 7-6 West Coast Conference), who have won six straight. Austin also had six assists. Mike Meadows had 12 points. Alphonso Anderson scored a career-high 26 points and had nine rebounds for the Tigers (8-20, 3-10). Nick Blake added 14 points. The Pilots improve to 2-0 against the Tigers for the season. Portland defeated Pacific 64-56 on Jan. 27. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ Portions of this story were generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
